The Roman empirO was divided between these chiefS‚ and the Adriatic was covered with their fleets. A battle was expected, which was to decide the fate of the empire. On the eve of this dreadful scene, Horace composed uiis epode, in which he deplores the condition of the Roman peo- pIe, and intimates that they may as well abandon their country for ever, as live amidst such scenes of horror and uncertainty. In short, the civil wars, which began between Marius and Sylla ln the year 666 of Rome, were never perfectly extinguished till the death of Antony in 724.
